<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-08-05T10:25:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-08-05T10:25:00-05:00" n="612" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d612">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/743: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Engert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-05T18:00:00+02:35">August 5, 1935—6 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received August 5—2:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>69. At an audience I had this afternoon with the Emperor he
                                    expressed gratitude for the statement made by the President on
                                    August 1st which he considers typical of the love of peace of
                                    the American people. His Majesty also referred in kindly terms
                                    to the helpful work of the American missionaries in
                                    Ethiopia.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>